'''Eric R. Pratt''' (born January 23, 1964) is a [[Minnesota]] politician and member of the [[Minnesota Senate]]. A member of the [[Republican Party of Minnesota]], he represents District 55 in the southwestern [[Twin Cities]] metropolitan area.

==Early life, education, and career==
Pratt's family moved to [[Prior Lake, Minnesota]] in 1978, where he graduated from [[Prior Lake High School]].<ref name="about">{{cite web | url=http://www.ericprattmn.com/meeteric.html | title=Meet Eric Pratt | publisher=Pratt for Minnesota | accessdate=May 10, 2013}}</ref> He attended the [[University of Colorado Boulder]], graduating in 1987 with a [[Bachelor of Arts|B.A.]] in [[economics]] and later the [[University of St. Thomas (Minnesota)|University of St. Thomas]], graduating in 1993 with a [[Master of Business Administration|M.B.A.]]<ref name="patch">{{cite web | url=http://shakopee.patch.com/articles/eric-pratt-republican-candidate-senate-district-55 | title=Eric Pratt Republican Candidate Senate District 55 | work=Shakopee Patch | date=July 30, 2012 | accessdate=May 10, 2013 | author=Baumann, Lisa}}</ref>

He was a member of the Prior Lake-Savage School Board from 2000 to 2012 and served as its chair.<ref name="about" /><ref name="patch" />

==Minnesota Senate==
Pratt was first elected to the [[Minnesota Senate]] in 2012.<ref name="Pratt">{{cite web | url=http://www.leg.state.mn.us/legdb/fulldetail.aspx?ID=15386 | title=Pratt, Eric R. | publisher=Minnesota Legislative Reference Library | work=Legislators Past & Present | accessdate=May 10, 2013}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Pratt is married to his wife, Tina. They have two children and reside in [[Prior Lake, Minnesota]]. Pratt is a [[risk manager]].<ref name="Pratt" />

